{
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "- Thank you, sir.\n- Alright. See you later, thanks.",
            "start": 0.594,
            "duration": 2.112
        },
        {
            "text": "Hi, my name is Tony",
            "start": 2.89,
            "duration": 1.414
        },
        {
            "text": "and this is Every Frame a Painting.",
            "start": 4.305,
            "duration": 1.519
        },
        {
            "text": "Today's topic is the oner, AKA a long take.",
            "start": 6.078,
            "duration": 3.426
        },
        {
            "text": "This is probably the most jerked-off-to\ntype of shot in filmmaking.",
            "start": 9.504,
            "duration": 3.777
        },
        {
            "text": "But basically, all it means",
            "start": 13.281,
            "duration": 1.593
        },
        {
            "text": "is doing an entire scene\nin a single, unbroken shot.",
            "start": 14.874,
            "duration": 3.074
        },
        {
            "text": "And let's face it, it's pretty awesome.",
            "start": 17.948,
            "duration": 2.06
        },
        {
            "text": "We all have our favorites.",
            "start": 20.008,
            "duration": 1.424
        },
        {
            "text": "There's six dozen lists\non the internet about this.",
            "start": 21.457,
            "duration": 2.687
        },
        {
            "text": "But we tend to notice the ones\nthat draw attention to themselves.",
            "start": 24.144,
            "duration": 2.819
        },
        {
            "text": "So let's skip all of these guys",
            "start": 26.963,
            "duration": 2.09
        },
        {
            "text": "and go to one filmmaker\nwho does oners all the time,",
            "start": 29.053,
            "duration": 3.103
        },
        {
            "text": "except his goal is to remain invisible.",
            "start": 32.156,
            "duration": 2.12
        },
        {
            "text": "This dude.",
            "start": 35.22,
            "duration": 0.906
        },
        {
            "text": "Truthfully, Spielberg's takes\naren't even that long.",
            "start": 37.014,
            "duration": 2.499
        },
        {
            "text": "He tends to keep them less than 3 minutes.",
            "start": 39.852,
            "duration": 2.164
        },
        {
            "text": "In fact, he really likes that\none minute to two-minute zone,",
            "start": 42.016,
            "duration": 2.837
        },
        {
            "text": "which is long enough to\ncover an entire scene,",
            "start": 44.853,
            "duration": 2.363
        },
        {
            "text": "but short enough to keep the pace brisk.",
            "start": 47.216,
            "duration": 2.249
        },
        {
            "text": "And while other directors seem to have",
            "start": 49.465,
            "duration": 1.852
        },
        {
            "text": "a dominant formal technique\nto their long takes \u2014",
            "start": 51.318,
            "duration": 2.144
        },
        {
            "text": "for instance, Wes Anderson\nlikes to move laterally,",
            "start": 53.486,
            "duration": 2.479
        },
        {
            "text": "the only thing that really\ndefines a Spielberg oner",
            "start": 55.965,
            "duration": 2.702
        },
        {
            "text": "is that it's supposed to be invisible.",
            "start": 58.692,
            "duration": 2.505
        },
        {
            "text": "So maybe I'm full of shit\nfor even saying it exists.",
            "start": 61.77,
            "duration": 2.499
        },
        {
            "text": "Now, I'm gonna cut\nthese shots down for this video,",
            "start": 64.718,
            "duration": 2.18
        },
        {
            "text": "but if you want to see the full scenes,",
            "start": 66.899,
            "duration": 1.286
        },
        {
            "text": "I've put them all in two\nseparate videos linked below.",
            "start": 68.186,
            "duration": 2.497
        },
        {
            "text": "First off, a shot from\nRaiders of the Lost Ark.",
            "start": 71.71,
            "duration": 2.513
        },
        {
            "text": "This is a single unbroken, 90-second take.",
            "start": 74.224,
            "duration": 2.566
        },
        {
            "text": "The great thing about it is that it's\nbasically four different shots in one:",
            "start": 77.379,
            "duration": 3.35
        },
        {
            "text": "there's a push-in, two matching\nsingles, and an insert.",
            "start": 80.752,
            "duration": 3.328
        },
        {
            "text": "So Spielberg combines all four\ninto a single moving master.",
            "start": 84.08,
            "duration": 3.581
        },
        {
            "text": "It's really simple and elegant,",
            "start": 87.661,
            "duration": 2.094
        },
        {
            "text": "and it probably saved\na bunch of time on set.",
            "start": 89.755,
            "duration": 2.699
        },
        {
            "text": "Also, it really works for the scene,",
            "start": 92.805,
            "duration": 1.785
        },
        {
            "text": "because there's suspense\nin the drinking contest.",
            "start": 94.591,
            "duration": 2.323
        },
        {
            "text": "And no matter how many times I watch it,",
            "start": 96.938,
            "duration": 1.578
        },
        {
            "text": "I still forget the exact timing,",
            "start": 98.516,
            "duration": 1.697
        },
        {
            "text": "so it's always funny when this happens.",
            "start": 100.213,
            "duration": 2.184
        },
        {
            "text": "Next up is a shot from Minority Report.",
            "start": 105.203,
            "duration": 2.038
        },
        {
            "text": "This time, they're on a steadicam.",
            "start": 107.241,
            "duration": 1.707
        },
        {
            "text": "But notice how the camera\nnever moves unmotivated.",
            "start": 108.948,
            "duration": 2.297
        },
        {
            "text": "It's always following\na motion or an action.",
            "start": 111.245,
            "duration": 1.805
        },
        {
            "text": "Hold that, please.",
            "start": 113.05,
            "duration": 1.113
        },
        {
            "text": "The pacing is fantastic,",
            "start": 114.163,
            "duration": 1.321
        },
        {
            "text": "you really get the sense that\nthe scene is unfolding in front of you,",
            "start": 115.484,
            "duration": 2.755
        },
        {
            "text": "rather than a cameraman hitting his marks.",
            "start": 118.239,
            "duration": 2.363
        },
        {
            "text": "You're in a lot of trouble, John.",
            "start": 120.602,
            "duration": 1.458
        },
        {
            "text": "The blocking of the actors is really fluid",
            "start": 122.659,
            "duration": 1.719
        },
        {
            "text": "and the shot goes from\nfavoring one character...",
            "start": 124.403,
            "duration": 2.032
        },
        {
            "text": "...to favoring another.",
            "start": 127.557,
            "duration": 1.156
        },
        {
            "text": "Seems I've found a flaw.",
            "start": 128.713,
            "duration": 2.087
        },
        {
            "text": "Flashing back in time, this is Jaws.",
            "start": 132.268,
            "duration": 1.961
        },
        {
            "text": "The great thing about this one\nis how restrained it is.",
            "start": 134.229,
            "duration": 2.69
        },
        {
            "text": "The cameraman barely moves.",
            "start": 136.919,
            "duration": 1.909
        },
        {
            "text": "All of the movement is\nin the blocking of the actors",
            "start": 138.828,
            "duration": 2.25
        },
        {
            "text": "and specially, the really\nsmart choice of location.",
            "start": 141.103,
            "duration": 2.641
        },
        {
            "text": "By shooting on a real ferry,",
            "start": 144.017,
            "duration": 1.545
        },
        {
            "text": "Spielberg can use the background action\nto keep the pace snappy.",
            "start": 145.562,
            "duration": 2.885
        },
        {
            "text": "One of the reasons I forgot\nhow long this shot is",
            "start": 148.447,
            "duration": 1.938
        },
        {
            "text": "is because the background keeps shifting",
            "start": 150.385,
            "duration": 1.5
        },
        {
            "text": "and you're always looking\nat something new.",
            "start": 151.886,
            "duration": 2.235
        },
        {
            "text": "You yell \"shark\",",
            "start": 154.385,
            "duration": 1.389
        },
        {
            "text": "we've got a panic on our hands\non the 4th of July.",
            "start": 157.619,
            "duration": 2.455
        },
        {
            "text": "Next up, Saving Private Ryan.",
            "start": 160.783,
            "duration": 1.728
        },
        {
            "text": "One of the hallmarks of a Spielberg oner",
            "start": 164.786,
            "duration": 1.778
        },
        {
            "text": "is that he tends to do almost all of his\nspecial FX or his vis FX in the master.",
            "start": 166.564,
            "duration": 4.302
        },
        {
            "text": "And this one's a doozy.",
            "start": 170.866,
            "duration": 1.242
        },
        {
            "text": "Explosions, rubble, dust, smoke,\ngunfire, squibs, and you know...",
            "start": 172.108,
            "duration": 4.68
        },
        {
            "text": "A tank.",
            "start": 177.77,
            "duration": 0.883
        },
        {
            "text": "Good shit.",
            "start": 180.239,
            "duration": 0.906
        },
        {
            "text": "Now, I do want to emphasize,",
            "start": 181.833,
            "duration": 1.362
        },
        {
            "text": "Spielberg did not invent this type of shot.",
            "start": 183.195,
            "duration": 1.982
        },
        {
            "text": "In fact, it used to be\na very common choice.",
            "start": 185.177,
            "duration": 2.549
        },
        {
            "text": "How about you, handsome?",
            "start": 187.726,
            "duration": 1.158
        },
        {
            "text": "Haven't I seen you somewhere before?",
            "start": 190.067,
            "duration": 1.408
        },
        {
            "text": "In the 40s and 50s and 60s,",
            "start": 191.475,
            "duration": 1.766
        },
        {
            "text": "studio directors frequently employed",
            "start": 193.241,
            "duration": 1.852
        },
        {
            "text": "a moderate-length oner\nto move the story along.",
            "start": 195.093,
            "duration": 2.36
        },
        {
            "text": "How do you like this?\nI'm running outta alibis.",
            "start": 197.483,
            "duration": 2.034
        },
        {
            "text": "But really, beginning with\nRope and Touch of Evil,",
            "start": 199.517,
            "duration": 2.079
        },
        {
            "text": "the oner became a\ncalling card for directors.",
            "start": 201.596,
            "duration": 2.077
        },
        {
            "text": "Audiences noticed it,",
            "start": 203.673,
            "duration": 1.191
        },
        {
            "text": "film critics and students\ngot raging hard-ons for it,",
            "start": 204.864,
            "duration": 2.513
        },
        {
            "text": "and for the last 50 years,\nit's been a game of one-upmanship.",
            "start": 207.377,
            "duration": 2.722
        },
        {
            "text": "Yours is 3 minutes?\nWell mine's 17.",
            "start": 210.099,
            "duration": 2.329
        },
        {
            "text": "Hitchcock did a movie\nseemingly in one take?",
            "start": 213.084,
            "duration": 1.852
        },
        {
            "text": "Well we did it actually in one.",
            "start": 214.936,
            "duration": 1.93
        },
        {
            "text": "Now, I'm not saying that\nthese long takes are bad.",
            "start": 216.866,
            "duration": 2.435
        },
        {
            "text": "Most of them are fun as shit.",
            "start": 219.301,
            "duration": 1.614
        },
        {
            "text": "All of them are a little awe-inspiring.",
            "start": 220.915,
            "duration": 2.183
        },
        {
            "text": "But there used to be a real type of shot\nin at least American cinema that was\u2026",
            "start": 223.098,
            "duration": 4.093
        },
        {
            "text": "for lack of a better word, really robust.",
            "start": 227.191,
            "duration": 2.402
        },
        {
            "text": "Like, it didn't break down.",
            "start": 229.593,
            "duration": 1.403
        },
        {
            "text": "It worked, it got the job done.",
            "start": 230.996,
            "duration": 1.909
        },
        {
            "text": "It was always interesting to watch.",
            "start": 232.905,
            "duration": 1.827
        },
        {
            "text": "It didn't call attention to itself.",
            "start": 234.732,
            "duration": 2.005
        },
        {
            "text": "You know, you could rely on it.",
            "start": 236.737,
            "duration": 1.777
        },
        {
            "text": "Now, it's split.",
            "start": 239.205,
            "duration": 1.108
        },
        {
            "text": "You got one branch of filmmaking",
            "start": 240.313,
            "duration": 1.345
        },
        {
            "text": "that is trying to go faster,\nshorter, more chaotic.",
            "start": 241.658,
            "duration": 2.455
        },
        {
            "text": "And another that is almost\nwillfully doing the opposite.",
            "start": 244.113,
            "duration": 2.977
        },
        {
            "text": "Some people are still in the middle.",
            "start": 247.09,
            "duration": 1.31
        },
        {
            "text": "Alfonso Cuar\u00f3n comes to mind",
            "start": 248.4,
            "duration": 1.452
        },
        {
            "text": "as someone trying to mine\nthe long take for dramatic purposes.",
            "start": 249.853,
            "duration": 3.111
        },
        {
            "text": "But even Alfonso\nisn't trying to be invisible.",
            "start": 252.964,
            "duration": 2.711
        },
        {
            "text": "Hell, even Spielberg sometimes\nwants you to notice.",
            "start": 256.548,
            "duration": 2.279
        },
        {
            "text": "This one from Minority Report",
            "start": 258.827,
            "duration": 1.43
        },
        {
            "text": "is practically a De Palma\nor Hitchcock shot.",
            "start": 260.257,
            "duration": 2.736
        },
        {
            "text": "This one from Duel is, I mean,\nit's almost like a slasher movie.",
            "start": 262.993,
            "duration": 4.114
        },
        {
            "text": "This one from Always,",
            "start": 271.375,
            "duration": 1.081
        },
        {
            "text": "which is a terrible movie,",
            "start": 272.481,
            "duration": 1.543
        },
        {
            "text": "is done in sync with a 747.",
            "start": 274.024,
            "duration": 2.578
        },
        {
            "text": "And this is just insane.",
            "start": 284.297,
            "duration": 2.158
        },
        {
            "text": "But otherwise, Spielberg plays it quiet.",
            "start": 291.281,
            "duration": 1.631
        },
        {
            "text": "Which is weird to say, because\nyou know, Spielberg.",
            "start": 292.912,
            "duration": 2.385
        },
        {
            "text": "But compared to his peers,",
            "start": 295.85,
            "duration": 1.085
        },
        {
            "text": "this technique, which he has been doing\nthis for 40 years at this point,",
            "start": 296.935,
            "duration": 2.771
        },
        {
            "text": "makes him stand out all the more.",
            "start": 299.706,
            "duration": 1.544
        },
        {
            "text": "Which car were you planning on?",
            "start": 301.275,
            "duration": 2.49
        },
        {
            "text": "Whichever one you are.",
            "start": 305.796,
            "duration": 1.203
        },
        {
            "text": "So I guess that's maybe the closest\nI can get to defining a Spielberg oner.",
            "start": 307.0,
            "duration": 3.608
        },
        {
            "text": "It uses any and all possible\ntricks to remain invisible.",
            "start": 310.609,
            "duration": 3.114
        },
        {
            "text": "So if you're a director",
            "start": 314.273,
            "duration": 0.93
        },
        {
            "text": "and you want to pull off a Spielberg oner,",
            "start": 315.203,
            "duration": 1.655
        },
        {
            "text": "there\u2019s only a few simple rules to follow.",
            "start": 316.858,
            "duration": 1.482
        },
        {
            "text": "First, move your actors.",
            "start": 319.006,
            "duration": 1.32
        },
        {
            "text": "Move 'em around.",
            "start": 320.326,
            "duration": 1.12
        },
        {
            "text": "Don't just have them stand there and talk",
            "start": 321.446,
            "duration": 1.694
        },
        {
            "text": "like they're in a 2014 blockbuster.",
            "start": 323.14,
            "duration": 1.813
        },
        {
            "text": "Don't mind him.",
            "start": 324.977,
            "duration": 1.055
        },
        {
            "text": "- English humor?\n- Scottish whiskey.",
            "start": 326.032,
            "duration": 2.218
        },
        {
            "text": "Second, follow that movement.",
            "start": 328.275,
            "duration": 1.684
        },
        {
            "text": "The camera doesn't have\nto follow on a leash,",
            "start": 329.978,
            "duration": 1.994
        },
        {
            "text": "it can swing around,\nit can move counter to them,",
            "start": 331.972,
            "duration": 2.17
        },
        {
            "text": "it can track laterally, whatever.",
            "start": 334.143,
            "duration": 1.88
        },
        {
            "text": "But watch the scene and\nplace the camera accordingly.",
            "start": 336.024,
            "duration": 2.457
        },
        {
            "text": "Third, break down the shot",
            "start": 340.138,
            "duration": 1.153
        },
        {
            "text": "into multiple compositions\nand smaller angles.",
            "start": 341.291,
            "duration": 2.339
        },
        {
            "text": "You are essentially linking\nfive or six different shots",
            "start": 343.63,
            "duration": 2.492
        },
        {
            "text": "into a single moving master.",
            "start": 346.123,
            "duration": 1.241
        },
        {
            "text": "So you can think in terms of",
            "start": 348.061,
            "duration": 1.531
        },
        {
            "text": "single, over-the-shoulder, insert, wide.",
            "start": 349.592,
            "duration": 2.767
        },
        {
            "text": "It all flows together.",
            "start": 352.384,
            "duration": 1.2
        },
        {
            "text": "Ah, Frank.",
            "start": 355.881,
            "duration": 1.297
        },
        {
            "text": "Oh, and if you can accomplish all this",
            "start": 357.212,
            "duration": 1.297
        },
        {
            "text": "without even moving the camera?",
            "start": 358.509,
            "duration": 1.655
        },
        {
            "text": "Even better.",
            "start": 360.164,
            "duration": 0.892
        },
        {
            "text": "All of you?",
            "start": 361.602,
            "duration": 0.807
        },
        {
            "text": "Fourth, do your vis FX or special FX,",
            "start": 363.822,
            "duration": 2.334
        },
        {
            "text": "anything you need to\nkeep the \"magic\" alive,",
            "start": 366.157,
            "duration": 1.914
        },
        {
            "text": "do it in the wide shot.",
            "start": 368.072,
            "duration": 1.283
        },
        {
            "text": "Don't cheat and construct your elements",
            "start": 369.355,
            "duration": 1.891
        },
        {
            "text": "out of close-ups and cutaways,",
            "start": 371.246,
            "duration": 1.441
        },
        {
            "text": "put 'em in the wide shot and\nlet the actors interact with them.",
            "start": 372.687,
            "duration": 2.686
        },
        {
            "text": "And don't fucking green screen\nshit that should be practical",
            "start": 375.373,
            "duration": 2.698
        },
        {
            "text": "The audience can tell",
            "start": 378.071,
            "duration": 0.974
        },
        {
            "text": "when an actor is reacting\nto something that's there",
            "start": 379.045,
            "duration": 2.048
        },
        {
            "text": "versus something that isn't.",
            "start": 381.093,
            "duration": 1.156
        },
        {
            "text": "Fifth, if you need to, shoot a cutaway.",
            "start": 388.085,
            "duration": 2.102
        },
        {
            "text": "All of the shots in this video\nare completely unbroken takes,",
            "start": 390.187,
            "duration": 2.48
        },
        {
            "text": "but Spielberg isn't stupid.",
            "start": 392.667,
            "duration": 1.533
        },
        {
            "text": "He often shoots an insert\nor a cutaway for a oner",
            "start": 394.2,
            "duration": 1.867
        },
        {
            "text": "even if he's sure they nailed it.",
            "start": 396.696,
            "duration": 1.454
        },
        {
            "text": "This gives him the ability to\ntighten in editing if he needs to,",
            "start": 398.15,
            "duration": 3.007
        },
        {
            "text": "or perhaps use the beginning of one take",
            "start": 401.157,
            "duration": 2.092
        },
        {
            "text": "and the end of another.",
            "start": 403.25,
            "duration": 1.0
        },
        {
            "text": "It also helps if he needs someone",
            "start": 404.817,
            "duration": 1.141
        },
        {
            "text": "to hit a particularly difficult mark,",
            "start": 405.958,
            "duration": 1.787
        },
        {
            "text": "like making a gun land in the right spot.",
            "start": 407.745,
            "duration": 2.067
        },
        {
            "text": "...cautious fellow I am.",
            "start": 410.237,
            "duration": 1.476
        },
        {
            "text": "And last, keep it short.",
            "start": 413.787,
            "duration": 1.308
        },
        {
            "text": "Don't outstay your welcome.",
            "start": 415.095,
            "duration": 1.222
        },
        {
            "text": "The Spielberg oner is designed\nto get through scenes quickly",
            "start": 416.317,
            "duration": 2.293
        },
        {
            "text": "and keep the pace up.",
            "start": 418.611,
            "duration": 0.804
        },
        {
            "text": "You should not be\nspending an entire day",
            "start": 419.813,
            "duration": 1.607
        },
        {
            "text": "trying to get it perfect.",
            "start": 421.445,
            "duration": 1.157
        },
        {
            "text": "That's for shit like this.",
            "start": 422.602,
            "duration": 1.167
        },
        {
            "text": "So in conclusion,",
            "start": 426.635,
            "duration": 1.302
        },
        {
            "text": "I understand that there's\nsometimes a lot of backlash",
            "start": 427.937,
            "duration": 2.077
        },
        {
            "text": "with regards to talking about\nSpielberg as a serious artist.",
            "start": 430.039,
            "duration": 2.663
        },
        {
            "text": "I mean, sometimes the sentimental\nstuff is a little hard to swallow.",
            "start": 432.702,
            "duration": 3.018
        },
        {
            "text": "I'm not gonna talk about his legacy,",
            "start": 436.29,
            "duration": 1.421
        },
        {
            "text": "but I do think he should be\ncelebrated for his oners.",
            "start": 437.711,
            "duration": 2.348
        },
        {
            "text": "Especially considering it's a technique",
            "start": 440.52,
            "duration": 1.477
        },
        {
            "text": "generally abandoned by mainstream directors",
            "start": 441.997,
            "duration": 2.125
        },
        {
            "text": "for either this kinda\nincomprehensible bullshit",
            "start": 444.122,
            "duration": 2.823
        },
        {
            "text": "or this really good, but also\nreally noticeable style.",
            "start": 448.165,
            "duration": 3.425
        },
        {
            "text": "Ironically, this dude,",
            "start": 453.282,
            "duration": 1.26
        },
        {
            "text": "who was once considered responsible\nfor destroying 70's Hollywood filmmaking,",
            "start": 454.567,
            "duration": 3.608
        },
        {
            "text": "is probably the greatest\nliving practitioner",
            "start": 458.175,
            "duration": 2.467
        },
        {
            "text": "of a classic Hollywood tradition.",
            "start": 460.642,
            "duration": 1.536
        },
        {
            "text": "I wonder if he feels sad about that.",
            "start": 463.005,
            "duration": 1.568
        },
        {
            "text": "Fuck that, he's rich!",
            "start": 467.434,
            "duration": 1.724
        },
        {
            "text": "Subtitles by the Amara.org community",
            "start": 476.0,
            "duration": 3.0
        }
    ]
